<p>I have my image defined in an ImageView in layout XML file as follows:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;RelativeLayout     xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"     android:orientation="vertical"     android:layout_width="200dp"     android:layout_height="200dp"     android:gravity="center"     android:layout_margin="1dp"     android:background="@drawable/bg"&gt;  &lt;ImageView     android:layout_width="300dp"     android:layout_height="300dp"     android:id="@+id/imgId"     android:src="@drawable/img1"/&gt; ... &lt;/RelativeLayout&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I access ImageView object with id imgId inside my BroadCastReceiver class when I receive a broadcast?</p>  <pre><code>public class MyIntentReceiver extends BroadcastReceiver {      @Override     public void onReceive(Context context, Intent intent) {     ...     } } </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to access layout XML elements using RemoteViews?</p>  <pre><code>RemoteViews updateViews = new RemoteViews(context.getPackageName(), R.layout.mylayout); </code></pre>